result.execSummary:
The defendant Tye J. Parris was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant enters no contest plea.   Court reads on waiver of rights and tendering plea. Waiver free and voluntary. Court finds that a factual basis for the plea exists and finds defendant guilty. Michlig/Hogan/Defendant/Court statement to sentencing.

Adj. 4:10 P.M.  Review hearing scheduled for January 4, 2016 at 03:00 pm.

1:37 p.m. Defendant Tye J. Parris in court, via video, with attorney Mary L.R. Burns.  Michael William Schiek appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Burns states not sure if there are conflicts but appearing specially at this hearing - defendant qualifies for PD.  Burns moves to modify cash bond to signature bond.  Schiek statement to bond.  Defendant statement to Texas probation - Court states information provided to him is that defendant is on abscounder status from State of Texas on felony case. Court does not modify bond. In receipt of complaint, waive reading - not guilty plea 
Bail continued  Pre-trial conference scheduled for October 27, 2015 at 03:30 pm.
No abusive contact with Kayla Parris

1:36 p.m. Defendant Tye J. Parris in court, in custody via video.  Steven Mitchell Michlig appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant in receipt of complaint, right to counsel. Michlig statement to bail. Defendant currently on probation in Texas. Court questions defendant's connection to family in Rhinelander; wife's mother & dad live in the area; currently employed. Michlig statement/defendant currently in absconder status from Texas. Court statement to bond--sets $500 cash bond.  Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for October 2, 2015 at 01:15 pm.
